episodes.title: Joy Villa Interview: “Why I Had to Leave Scientology”
episodes.description:
In this interview, singer and author Joy Villa opens up about her decision to leave the Church of Scientology after years on the inside. From Grammy red carpets to navigating fame under the watchful eye of a high-control group, Joy shares the deeply personal story behind her departure—and the healing that followed.

We talk about her upcoming book, the manipulation she didn’t see until it was too late, and what life looks like after leaving one of the most controversial organizations in the world.

Grab your coffee, grab your emotional support animal, and let’s talk culty.

episodes.title: Scientology’s Dirty Deal BLOCKED: Meet the Man Who Shut Them Down
episodes.description:
Scientology thought they could quietly buy a city street in Clearwater, Florida—right in front of their planned L. Ron Hubbard Hall. But local activist Brooks Gibbs said absolutely not. In this interview, Brooks breaks down how he and community leader Barbara Sorey-Love rallied public support, fought back, and forced Scientology to withdraw their offer.

The goal? To protect the cultural legacy of Clearwater’s Black community by creating a memorial garden instead of letting Scientology expand their control.

We talk strategy, shady backroom deals, and how Save the Garden outmaneuvered one of the most powerful cults in America.

💥 Grab your coffee, grab your emotional support animal, and let’s talk culty.

👇 Let me know in the comments: Would your city have sold the street to Scientology?

episodes.title: Scientology Horror: I Was a Child Prisoner on L. Ron Hubbard’s Ship
episodes.description:
At just 11 years old, Danielle Chamberlain was sent to Scientology’s infamous Sea Org—alone, terrified, and trapped aboard L. Ron Hubbard’s ship, Apollo. What she endured was nothing short of child abuse, from brutal punishments to being locked in the ship’s hull for days, surviving on scraps of food. Danielle witnessed horrific cruelty, including people thrown overboard as punishment and a young boy screaming for hours while locked away.

In this interview, Danielle shares the shocking truth about her time in Scientology’s secretive world, how she escaped the cult, and the lifelong trauma she still carries.

🔴 What really happened aboard Apollo?
🔴 Why did Scientology target children for the Sea Org?
🔴 How did L. Ron Hubbard control and manipulate his followers?

🚨 WATCH NOW as Danielle exposes Scientology’s darkest secrets! 🚨

#Scientology #SeaOrg #ScientologyExposed #CultSurvivor #LRonHubbard #ScientologyHorror #ExScientology #LifeAfterScientology #CultAwareness

Think you’re too smart to fall for a cult? Think again! Cults, high-control groups, and online extremist movements use mind control, manipulation, and psychological tactics that can lure in anyone—yes, even you!

In this livestream, I’m joined by Jon Atack, ex-Scientologist and author of Let’s Sell These People a Piece of Blue Sky, to break down how cults recruit, brainwash, and trap people in their web of control. We’ll expose the red flags, share shocking real-life examples, and discuss how to protect yourself and your loved ones from undue influence.

📌 TOPICS WE COVER:

The psychological tricks cults use to recruit smart people
Scientology’s manipulation tactics and how they mirror other cults
How online movements and conspiracy groups use mind control
